<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Assist" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Assist,</orth> vb. trans., 1) to help: <cit><quote>how can they then a. me in the act?</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 350" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 350</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 7, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.6.3" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 3, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 101</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 92.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.196" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 28</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.247" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 1, 19</bibl>. Absolutely: <cit><quote>a., good friends,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.15.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 15, 31</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to attend, to join: <cit><quote>the king and prince at prayers! let us a. them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 1, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>midnight, a. our moan,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 3, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>yourself, --ed with your honoured friends, bring them to our embracement,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 113</bibl></cit>. Absolutely: <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 156</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>